          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            Even without the sending off, Bayern would've won comfortably. This is a fairer representation of the gulf in class between the (current) top 2 sides in Germany than the previous 15 games and I'm not surprised Bayern won. It was interesting to see Thiago play further forward but I still think 4-3-3 would be the best for this group of players. Carlo has been a 4-3-3 man for a while but I remember when he had a different formation at Milan (which our media dubbed the Christmas tree) and also tried a few other setups to counter the opposition (4-3-1-2, 4-4-2...), so he isn't an obstinate manager to the degree it harms his teams. Bayern have the players to play in a number of formations so Carlo has a luxury in that regards. Really hoping for a drop in form after the winter break but it's good to see Bayern improving.
